Author: internerderner2
Text: It happens to me with Diet Coke. After years of drinking it on the daily I had a sip of regular Coke (obviously I logged the calories of a whole can) and really tasted funny.  When it comes to actual food though...meh. I can train myself to *believe* the low-cal version is nicer, but deep, very very deep down there's always that voice inside me that says "no it's not and you know it but whatever".

Author: MuddyWalruss
Text: This is me with yogurt. The normal one i get has 40 cals per 100g (so 400 for the whole tub) and when i tried the higher calorie version i couldn't swallow it, it was horrendous.
